<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  T197: excludes generated/non-production code from the backend coverage
  denominator so the T190 ratchet is more sensitive to real regressions.

  - ExcludeByFile: EF Core migrations (Migrations/*.cs, including the
    generated Designer.cs and ModelSnapshot.cs siblings coverlet would
    otherwise count as coverable-but-never-exercised) and everything under
    any obj/ intermediate build directory (GlobalUsings.g.cs, AssemblyInfo.cs,
    etc. — real compiled sequence points, zero real logic).
  - Exclude: the Seeder tool by assembly — deploy-time content-import
    tooling, not application code any test suite exercises or should be
    expected to.

  Deliberately does NOT use ExcludeByAttribute (GeneratedCodeAttribute /
  CompilerGeneratedAttribute): empirically confirmed (T197) to be far too
  broad in this codebase — it drops entire FILES, not just individual
  generated members, once a class's only remaining coverable content is a
  compiler-generated construct. This codebase's pervasive use of "record"
  types and primary constructors means large numbers of genuinely
  meaningful classes have compiler-generated equality/constructor members
  as their sole instrumented sequence points; excluding by that attribute
  measured 37 assemblies / 320 classes collapsing to 15 assemblies / 95
  classes on this codebase's Unit suite alone (CompilerGeneratedAttribute)
  or 33/211 (GeneratedCodeAttribute alone) — both silently deleting real,
  untested production code from the denominator rather than narrowly
  excluding tool-generated boilerplate. ExcludeByFile + assembly-scoped
  Exclude, tested in isolation, behave exactly as expected (37 assemblies
  unchanged, ~63 fewer files matching the migrations/Seeder file count) —
  those are the only mechanisms used here.

  Referenced via the "settings" flag (backend/coverlet.runsettings) on every
  "dotnet test" coverage-collecting invocation (CI and local). Does not
  change what tests run or their pass/fail outcome — only what coverlet
  counts as coverable.
-->
<RunSettings>
  <DataCollectionRunSettings>
    <DataCollectors>
      <DataCollector friendlyName="XPlat code coverage">
        <Configuration>
          <Format>cobertura</Format>
          <Exclude>[SpecPour.Tools.Seeder]*</Exclude>
          <ExcludeByFile>**/Migrations/*.cs,**/obj/**/*.cs</ExcludeByFile>
        </Configuration>
      </DataCollector>
    </DataCollectors>
  </DataCollectionRunSettings>
</RunSettings>
